  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "Frontmatter is a block of structured metadata placed at the top of a Markdown file, delimited by a pair of --- lines. The content between the delimiters is written in YAML (a human-readable data format) and provides machine-readable information about the document.\nA typical frontmatter block looks like this:\n--- title: \u0026#34;Example Note\u0026#34; date-created: 2025-06-15 tags: - type/term --- Everything above the closing --- is metadata; everything below it is the document\u0026rsquo;s body content. Markdown processors and static site generators read the frontmatter to determine how to render, categorize, and link the document.\n",
  "name": "frontmatter",
